unless the project specifically requires a benchmark study.

Why Customers Don't Get Irritated

Customers care about:

Accuracy
Delivery time
Business value

They don't care whether you tested 2 models or 20 models internally.

A professional update would be:

"We evaluated several forecasting approaches and selected the best-performing model based on prediction accuracy."

The customer sees the result, not every experiment.
----------------------------------------------------


In academic projects, multiple models are tested to compare performance and understand different forecasting techniques. 
In industry projects, model selection is driven by business requirements and time constraints. Usually, 
only a few suitable models are evaluated, and the best one is chosen based on accuracy, interpretability, and deployment requirements.

